DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl"
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(3,7,2);
$b = random(2,8,2);
$i = random(2,4,1);
$c = $i*$b;
$m = -$b/$a;
$j = random(4,6,1);
$x = $j*$b;
$y = $a*$j-$i;
$k = $y - $m*$x;
$ans = "-$b/$a x + $k";

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 16:
$BR $SPACE $BR
Find an equation for the linear function $BITALIC g(x) $EITALIC which is perpendicular to the line \( $a x - $b y = $c \) and intersects the line \( $a x - $b y = $c \) at \( x = $x \).
$BR
$BR
\( g(x) = \ \) \{ ans_rule(25) \}
END_TEXT

ANS( fun_cmp($ans,vars=>'x'));

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR
$BBOLD SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR
First we place the line \( $a x - $b y = $c \) into slope-intercept form:
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
\( $a x - $b y = $c \)
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
\( $b y = $a x - $c \)
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
\( y = \frac{$a}{$b} x - \frac{$c}{$b} \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
The slope of this line is \( m = \frac{$a}{$b} \ \). Since the graph of $BITALIC g(x) $EITALIC is perpendicular to it, the slope of $BITALIC g(x) $EITALIC is
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
\( m = -\frac{1}{$a / $b} = - \frac{$b}{$a} \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
We see from the first equation that at \( x = $x \),
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
\( y = \frac{$a}{$b} ($x) - \frac{$c}{$b} = $y \)
$BR
so the graph of the first equation contains the point ($x, $y).  Since the graph of $BITALIC g(x) $EITALIC also contains this point, we have
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
\( g($x) = b+ m($x) = $y \)
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
\( b + (-$b / $a)($x) = $y \)
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
\( b = $y + ($b / $a)($x) \)
$BR
$SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE $SPACE
\( b = $k \) ,
$BR $SPACE $BR
so \( g(x) = - \frac{$b}{$a} x + $k \).
$BR
END_SOLUTION


ENDDOCUMENT();   # This should be the last executable line in the problem.